    How to mend split ends naturally?
    Coconut oil is fully of super healthy fatty acid which makes it a very good DIY home remedy to temporarily merge split ends. Simply take 1--2 tablespoons of coconut oil and melt it slowly in a microwave or over a double boiler on the stove. Allow oil to cool so it's not too hot to the touch. Apply to the ends.Jun 17, 2015

    Do split ends repair?
    Split ends in hair cannot be truly repaired. The best and most effective solution is to cut them off. Once hair has split, the damage is permanent, and attempting to repair split ends with products will only provide temporary results. However, you can take steps to minimize split ends in the future:May 20, 2020
